{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781758065602,"sessionID":"ses_126f83aa4ffekBSRvWmpN9g5Xg","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_Q7ynNYwe3Efb7Gc1ALfHQ1P8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review/lineages/gpt55-p017c004-2/review-report.md","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review/lineages/gpt55-p017c004-2/review-report.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Review Report - gpt55-p017c004-2\n2: \n3: ## Executive Summary\n4: \n5: Verdict: **CONDITIONAL**\n6: \n7: This one-iteration fan-out lineage reviewed the correctness of the confidence calibration labeled-set implementation. It found one active P1: the shipped loader accepts only a top-level labeled-pair array, while the bundled starter labeled-set artifact is an object containing metadata and `pairs`. Active counts: P0=0, P1=1, P2=0. Stop reason: `maxIterationsReached`. `hasAdvisories=false`.\n8: \n9: ## Planning Trigger\n10: \n11: Route to remediation planning for F001. The smallest safe fix is to either make `loadLabeledSet()` accept both `LabeledPair[]` and `{ pairs: LabeledPair[] }` with tests against the checked-in starter file, or change the generator/artifact to emit the exact array shape the loader requires.\n12: \n13: ## Active Finding Registry\n14: \n15: | ID | Severity | Dimension | Status | Evidence | Summary |\n16: |----|----------|-----------|--------|----------|---------|\n17: | F001 | P1 | correctness | active | `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/confidence-calibration.ts:73-76`; `.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/017-search-and-output-intelligence-implementation/004-confidence-calibration-labeled-set/assets/fit-calibration.mjs:168-181`; `.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/017-search-and-output-intelligence-implementation/004-confidence-calibration-labeled-set/assets/confidence-labeled-set.starter.json:1-5` | Starter labeled set cannot be loaded by the shipped loader without manual unwrapping. |\n18: \n19: ## Remediation Workstreams\n20: \n21: 1. Align starter data shape and loader contract.\n22: 2. Add a regression test that parses `assets/confidence-labeled-set.starter.json` and passes the result through the supported loader path.\n23: 3. Re-run the confidence-calibration tests and the target spec validation after the fix.\n24: \n25: ## Spec Seed\n26: \n27: - Clarify whether the canonical labeled-set file format is `LabeledPair[]` or an object with metadata plus `pairs`.\n28: - If metadata is retained, document the loader accepting the wrapper shape.\n29: \n30: ## Plan Seed\n31: \n32: - Update `loadLabeledSet()` or `fit-calibration.mjs` so the generated starter artifact and loader agree.\n33: - Extend `confidence-calibration.vitest.ts` with a fixture read of the shipped starter asset.\n34: - Re-run the confidence calibration unit tests and strict validation for the target packet.\n35: \n36: ## Traceability Status\n37: \n38: | Protocol | Gate | Status | Notes |\n39: |----------|------|--------|-------|\n40: | spec_code | hard | partial | Rebalance/default-off wiring is present; starter-set loader path has F001. |\n41: | checklist_evidence | hard | partial | Task rows are checked, but validation commands were not run in this lineage. |\n42: | feature_catalog_code | advisory | pending | Not covered before maxIterations. |\n43: | playbook_capability | advisory | pending | Not covered before maxIterations. |\n44: \n45: ## Deferred Items\n46: \n47: - Security, maintainability, and full traceability dimensions were not covered in this one-iteration lineage.\n48: - No P2 advisories were recorded.\n49: - No target `resource-map.md` existed at init, so the resource-map coverage gate was skipped.\n50: \n51: ## Audit Appendix\n52: \n53: | Item | Result |\n54: |------|--------|\n55: | Iterations completed | 1 |\n56: | Stop reason | maxIterationsReached |\n57: | Dimensions covered | 1 of 4 |\n58: | New findings ratio | 1.00 |\n59: | Claim adjudication | passed for F001 |\n60: | P0 replay | not applicable, no P0 findings |\n61: | Validation commands | not run due lineage write restriction |\n62: \n63: Replay verdict: activeP0=0 and activeP1=1 maps to CONDITIONAL. The release-readiness state remains `in-progress` because coverage is incomplete and a P1 remains active.\n\n(End of file - total 63 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Review Report - gpt55-p017c004-2\n\n## Executive Summary\n\nVerdict: **CONDITIONAL**\n\nThis one-iteration fan-out lineage reviewed the correctness of the confidence calibration labeled-set implementation. It found one active P1: the shipped loader accepts only a top-level labeled-pair array, while the bundled starter labeled-set artifact is an object containing metadata and `pairs`. Active counts: P0=0, P1=1, P2=0. Stop reason: `maxIterationsReached`. `hasAdvisories=false`.\n\n## Planning Trigger\n\nRoute to remediation planning for F001. The smallest safe fix is to either make `loadLabeledSet()` accept both `LabeledPair[]` and `{ pairs: LabeledPair[] }` with tests against the checked-in starter file, or change the generator/artifact to emit the exact array shape the loader requires.\n\n## Active Finding Registry\n\n| ID | Severity | Dimension | Status | Evidence | Summary |\n|----|----------|-----------|--------|----------|---------|\n| F001 | P1 | correctness | active | `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/confidence-calibration.ts:73-76`; `.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/017-search-and-output-intelligence-implementation/004-confidence-calibration-labeled-set/assets/fit-calibration.mjs:168-181`; `.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/017-search-and-output-intelligence-implementation/004-confidence-calibration-labeled-set/assets/confidence-labeled-set.starter.json:1-5` | Starter labeled set cannot be loaded by the shipped loader without manual unwrapping. |\n\n## Remediation Workstreams\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review/lineages/gpt55-p017c004-2/review-report.md","text":"# Deep Review Report - gpt55-p017c004-2\n\n## Executive Summary\n\nVerdict: **CONDITIONAL**\n\nThis one-iteration fan-out lineage reviewed the correctness of the confidence calibration labeled-set implementation. It found one active P1: the shipped loader accepts only a top-level labeled-pair array, while the bundled starter labeled-set artifact is an object containing metadata and `pairs`. Active counts: P0=0, P1=1, P2=0. Stop reason: `maxIterationsReached`. `hasAdvisories=false`.\n\n## Planning Trigger\n\nRoute to remediation planning for F001. The smallest safe fix is to either make `loadLabeledSet()` accept both `LabeledPair[]` and `{ pairs: LabeledPair[] }` with tests against the checked-in starter file, or change the generator/artifact to emit the exact array shape the loader requires.\n\n## Active Finding Registry\n\n| ID | Severity | Dimension | Status | Evidence | Summary |\n|----|----------|-----------|--------|----------|---------|\n| F001 | P1 | correctness | active | `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/confidence-calibration.ts:73-76`; `.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/017-search-and-output-intelligence-implementation/004-confidence-calibration-labeled-set/assets/fit-calibration.mjs:168-181`; `.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/017-search-and-output-intelligence-implementation/004-confidence-calibration-labeled-set/assets/confidence-labeled-set.starter.json:1-5` | Starter labeled set cannot be loaded by the shipped loader without manual unwrapping. |\n\n## Remediation Workstreams\n\n1. Align starter data shape and loader contract.\n2. Add a regression test that parses `assets/confidence-labeled-set.starter.json` and passes the result through the supported loader path.\n3. Re-run the confidence-calibration tests and the target spec validation after the fix.\n\n## Spec Seed\n\n- Clarify whether the canonical labeled-set file format is `LabeledPair[]` or an object with metadata plus `pairs`.\n- If metadata is retained, document the loader accepting the wrapper shape.\n\n## Plan Seed\n\n- Update `loadLabeledSet()` or `fit-calibration.mjs` so the generated starter artifact and loader agree.\n- Extend `confidence-calibration.vitest.ts` with a fixture read of the shipped starter asset.\n- Re-run the confidence calibration unit tests and strict validation for the target packet.\n\n## Traceability Status\n\n| Protocol | Gate | Status | Notes |\n|----------|------|--------|-------|\n| spec_code | hard | partial | Rebalance/default-off wiring is present; starter-set loader path has F001. |\n| checklist_evidence | hard | partial | Task rows are checked, but validation commands were not run in this lineage. |\n| feature_catalog_code | advisory | pending | Not covered before maxIterations. |\n| playbook_capability | advisory | pending | Not covered before maxIterations. |\n\n## Deferred Items\n\n- Security, maintainability, and full traceability dimensions were not covered in this one-iteration lineage.\n- No P2 advisories were recorded.\n- No target `resource-map.md` existed at init, so the resource-map coverage gate was skipped.\n\n## Audit Appendix\n\n| Item | Result |\n|------|--------|\n| Iterations completed | 1 |\n| Stop reason | maxIterationsReached |\n| Dimensions covered | 1 of 4 |\n| New findings ratio | 1.00 |\n| Claim adjudication | passed for F001 |\n| P0 replay | not applicable, no P0 findings |\n| Validation commands | not run due lineage write restriction |\n\nReplay verdict: activeP0=0 and activeP1=1 maps to CONDITIONAL. The release-readiness state remains `in-progress` because coverage is incomplete and a P1 remains active.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":63,"totalLines":63,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review/lineages/gpt55-p017c004-2/review-report.md","time":{"start":1781758065591,"end":1781758065602}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0ff5c10620befa3b016a3378717ba481918bca2e28723d6beb"}},"id":"prt_ed90e7bb6001TWEBWGoINqMvVL","sessionID":"ses_126f83aa4ffekBSRvWmpN9g5Xg","messageID":"msg_ed90e4641001QliKrPWSp8qjXe"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781758065604,"sessionID":"ses_126f83aa4ffekBSRvWmpN9g5Xg","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_gI059nJyBiJEwrQB59dgL2cN","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review/lineages/gpt55-p017c004-2/iterations/iteration-001.md","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review/lineages/gpt55-p017c004-2/iterations/iteration-001.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Iteration 1: Correctness\n2: \n3: ## Focus\n4: \n5: - Dimension: Correctness\n6: - Scope: confidence rebalance and calibration loader/wiring surfaces named by the target packet.\n7: - Boundaries: target files read-only; outputs only under the lineage artifact directory.\n8: \n9: ## Scorecard\n10: \n11: - Dimensions covered: correctness\n12: - Files reviewed: 8\n13: - New findings: P0=0 P1=1 P2=0\n14: - Refined findings: P0=0 P1=0 P2=0\n15: - New findings ratio: 1.00\n16: \n17: ## Findings\n18: \n19: ### P0, Blocker\n20: \n21: - None.\n22: \n23: ### P1, Required\n24: \n25: - **F001**: Starter labeled set cannot be loaded by the shipped loader. `loadLabeledSet()` rejects anything that is not a top-level array [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/confidence-calibration.ts:73-76], but the bundled generator writes an object with metadata and a `pairs` array [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/017-search-and-output-intelligence-implementation/004-confidence-calibration-labeled-set/assets/fit-calibration.mjs:168-181], and the checked-in starter artifact has that object shape [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/017-search-and-output-intelligence-implementation/004-confidence-calibration-labeled-set/assets/confidence-labeled-set.starter.json:1-5]. This breaks the shipped end-to-end starter path unless every consumer manually unwraps `.pairs`, which is not covered by the loader contract or tests.\n26: \n27: ### P2, Suggestion\n28: \n29: - None.\n30: \n31: ## Claim Adjudication Packets\n32: \n33: ```json\n34: {\n35:   \"findingId\": \"F001\",\n36:   \"claim\": \"The bundled starter labeled-set artifact cannot be accepted by the shipped loadLabeledSet() API because the loader requires a top-level array while the generator and artifact emit an object containing pairs.\",\n37:   \"evidenceRefs\": [\n38:     \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/confidence-calibration.ts:73-76\",\n39:     \".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/017-search-and-output-intelligence-implementation/004-confidence-calibration-labeled-set/assets/fit-calibration.mjs:168-181\",\n40:     \".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/017-search-and-output-intelligence-implementation/004-confidence-calibration-labeled-set/assets/confidence-labeled-set.starter.json:1-5\"\n41:   ],\n42:   \"counterevidenceSought\": \"Read confidence-calibration.vitest.ts loader tests, fit-calibration.mjs writer code, the generated starter JSON header, spec.md scope, and implementation-summary.md delivery claims. No adapter or loader branch accepting { pairs: [...] } was found in the reviewed files.\",\n43:   \"alternativeExplanation\": \"The starter artifact may have been intended for human inspection with callers manually passing .pairs, but the delivered loader and tests do not document or enforce that adapter path, while the packet presents the starter set and loader as a shipped end-to-end path.\",\n44:   \"finalSeverity\": \"P1\",\n45:   \"confidence\": 0.88,\n46:   \"downgradeTrigger\": \"Downgrade to P2 if a documented consumer unwraps the pairs field before calling loadLabeledSet(), or if loadLabeledSet() is updated and tested to accept the generated starter artifact shape.\",\n47:   \"transitions\": [\n48:     {\n49:       \"iteration\": 1,\n50:       \"from\": null,\n51:       \"to\": \"P1\",\n52:       \"reason\": \"Initial discovery\"\n53:     }\n54:   ]\n55: }\n56: ```\n57: \n58: ## Cross-Reference Results\n59: \n60: | Protocol | Status | Gate | Evidence | Notes |\n61: |----------|--------|------|----------|-------|\n62: | spec_code | partial | hard | spec.md:78-79; confidence-calibration.ts:73-76 | Calibration infrastructure exists, but the starter labeled-set artifact does not load through the shipped loader. |\n63: | checklist_evidence | partial | hard | tasks.md:65-78 | Checked task rows exist; validation commands were not run in this lineage. |\n64: \n65: ## Assessment\n66: \n67: - New findings ratio: 1.00\n68: - Dimensions addressed: correctness\n69: - Novelty justification: one new P1 with direct source and artifact evidence.\n70: - Provisional verdict: CONDITIONAL\n71: \n72: ## Ruled Out\n73: \n74: - Calibration accidentally default-on: `maybeCalibrate()` returns early when `SPECKIT_CONFIDENCE_CALIBRATION` is not truthy and the flag helper is explicit opt-in.\n75: \n76: ## Dead Ends\n77: \n78: - Memory retrieval through the provided/blank session id failed with `E_SESSION_SCOPE`; direct packet/source reads were used instead.\n79: \n80: ## Recommended Next Focus\n81: \n82: Run traceability after remediating or accepting F001: check whether task completion criteria and implementation-summary verification claims still match the corrected starter-set path.\n83: Review verdict: CONDITIONAL\n\n(End of file - total 83 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Iteration 1: Correctness\n\n## Focus\n\n- Dimension: Correctness\n- Scope: confidence rebalance and calibration loader/wiring surfaces named by the target packet.\n- Boundaries: target files read-only; outputs only under the lineage artifact directory.\n\n## Scorecard\n\n- Dimensions covered: correctness\n- Files reviewed: 8\n- New findings: P0=0 P1=1 P2=0\n- Refined findings: P0=0 P1=0 P2=0\n- New findings ratio: 1.00\n\n## Findings\n\n### P0, Blocker\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review/lineages/gpt55-p017c004-2/iterations/iteration-001.md","text":"# Iteration 1: Correctness\n\n## Focus\n\n- Dimension: Correctness\n- Scope: confidence rebalance and calibration loader/wiring surfaces named by the target packet.\n- Boundaries: target files read-only; outputs only under the lineage artifact directory.\n\n## Scorecard\n\n- Dimensions covered: correctness\n- Files reviewed: 8\n- New findings: P0=0 P1=1 P2=0\n- Refined findings: P0=0 P1=0 P2=0\n- New findings ratio: 1.00\n\n## Findings\n\n### P0, Blocker\n\n- None.\n\n### P1, Required\n\n- **F001**: Starter labeled set cannot be loaded by the shipped loader. `loadLabeledSet()` rejects anything that is not a top-level array [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/confidence-calibration.ts:73-76], but the bundled generator writes an object with metadata and a `pairs` array [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/017-search-and-output-intelligence-implementation/004-confidence-calibration-labeled-set/assets/fit-calibration.mjs:168-181], and the checked-in starter artifact has that object shape [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/017-search-and-output-intelligence-implementation/004-confidence-calibration-labeled-set/assets/confidence-labeled-set.starter.json:1-5]. This breaks the shipped end-to-end starter path unless every consumer manually unwraps `.pairs`, which is not covered by the loader contract or tests.\n\n### P2, Suggestion\n\n- None.\n\n## Claim Adjudication Packets\n\n```json\n{\n  \"findingId\": \"F001\",\n  \"claim\": \"The bundled starter labeled-set artifact cannot be accepted by the shipped loadLabeledSet() API because the loader requires a top-level array while the generator and artifact emit an object containing pairs.\",\n  \"evidenceRefs\": [\n    \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/confidence-calibration.ts:73-76\",\n    \".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/017-search-and-output-intelligence-implementation/004-confidence-calibration-labeled-set/assets/fit-calibration.mjs:168-181\",\n    \".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/017-search-and-output-intelligence-implementation/004-confidence-calibration-labeled-set/assets/confidence-labeled-set.starter.json:1-5\"\n  ],\n  \"counterevidenceSought\": \"Read confidence-calibration.vitest.ts loader tests, fit-calibration.mjs writer code, the generated starter JSON header, spec.md scope, and implementation-summary.md delivery claims. No adapter or loader branch accepting { pairs: [...] } was found in the reviewed files.\",\n  \"alternativeExplanation\": \"The starter artifact may have been intended for human inspection with callers manually passing .pairs, but the delivered loader and tests do not document or enforce that adapter path, while the packet presents the starter set and loader as a shipped end-to-end path.\",\n  \"finalSeverity\": \"P1\",\n  \"confidence\": 0.88,\n  \"downgradeTrigger\": \"Downgrade to P2 if a documented consumer unwraps the pairs field before calling loadLabeledSet(), or if loadLabeledSet() is updated and tested to accept the generated starter artifact shape.\",\n  \"transitions\": [\n    {\n      \"iteration\": 1,\n      \"from\": null,\n      \"to\": \"P1\",\n      \"reason\": \"Initial discovery\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n## Cross-Reference Results\n\n| Protocol | Status | Gate | Evidence | Notes |\n|----------|--------|------|----------|-------|\n| spec_code | partial | hard | spec.md:78-79; confidence-calibration.ts:73-76 | Calibration infrastructure exists, but the starter labeled-set artifact does not load through the shipped loader. |\n| checklist_evidence | partial | hard | tasks.md:65-78 | Checked task rows exist; validation commands were not run in this lineage. |\n\n## Assessment\n\n- New findings ratio: 1.00\n- Dimensions addressed: correctness\n- Novelty justification: one new P1 with direct source and artifact evidence.\n- Provisional verdict: CONDITIONAL\n\n## Ruled Out\n\n- Calibration accidentally default-on: `maybeCalibrate()` returns early when `SPECKIT_CONFIDENCE_CALIBRATION` is not truthy and the flag helper is explicit opt-in.\n\n## Dead Ends\n\n- Memory retrieval through the provided/blank session id failed with `E_SESSION_SCOPE`; direct packet/source reads were used instead.\n\n## Recommended Next Focus\n\nRun traceability after remediating or accepting F001: check whether task completion criteria and implementation-summary verification claims still match the corrected starter-set path.\nReview verdict: CONDITIONAL","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":83,"totalLines":83,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review/lineages/gpt55-p017c004-2/iterations/iteration-001.md","time":{"start":1781758065593,"end":1781758065603}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0ff5c10620befa3b016a3378717bac819195e55b30a278b628"}},"id":"prt_ed90e7bb8001v6r6BdTJjujSRO","sessionID":"ses_126f83aa4ffekBSRvWmpN9g5Xg","messageID":"msg_ed90e4641001QliKrPWSp8qjXe"}}
